{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01CansfEqDDkXseXoMePhGsy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete and verified. \n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The \"transform capacity change\" was a config regression — the `es-transform-config` ConfigMap had `node.roles: [ ingest ]`, with the **`transform` role removed**, and the `es-transform` StatefulSet was scaled to `0`. With no transform-capable node in the cluster, the aggregation transform could not run (Elasticsearch reported *\"found no transform nodes\"*), so the aggregated view (`app-events-rollup`) went stale.\n\n**Remediation (capacity restored before restarting the job, per constraints):**\n1. **Restored transform capacity first** — patched `es-transform-config` to `node.roles: [ transform, remote_cluster_client ]` and scaled `es-transform` back to 1 replica. The node rejoined the cluster with role `rt` (transform + remote_cluster_client).\n2. **Created and started the transform** via the transform APIs (`PUT`/`POST _transform/events-by-service/_start`) — both `acknowledged: true`. No CRDs/ECK used; destination index untouched (it was newly built by the transform).\n\n**Verification — goal met:**\n- Transform `state: started`, running on node `es-transform-0`.\n- **Checkpoint advanced to `1`** (was `0` per the `transform-checkpoint` fixture), with `changes_last_detected_at` updating.\n- Destination index `app-events-rollup` is now populated with fresh aggregates: `api → 3`, `web → 2` (5 source docs processed, 2 indexed).\n\nThe aggregated view is live again and processing continues via the sync configuration."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1405,"cache_read_input_tokens":48251,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1405},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics